::: {.doc-subject}

Return a one-row model-summary DataFrame for a fitted model.
:::

::: {.doc-usage-source}
Usage

[Source](https://github.com/rich-iannone/greenwood/blob/main/greenwood/summaries/_registry.py#L195-L230){target="_blank" rel="noopener"}
:::

::: {.doc-signature .doc-Kind.FUNCTION}
```python
glance(model, **kwargs)
```
:::

::: {.doc-text}

Produces a single row of model-level statistics such as the number of observations,
number of events, log-likelihood, AIC, and concordance. This is the Python equivalent
of R's `broom::glance()`.
:::

## Parameters {.doc-parameters}

::: {.doc-definition-items}
<code>[model]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [object]{.doc-parameter-annotation}</code>

:   A fitted Greenwood estimator (e.g., `CoxPH`, `AFT`, `Parametric`).

<code>[**kwargs]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [Any]{.doc-parameter-annotation}</code>

:   Forwarded to the registered adapter. Common options include `format=`.
:::

## Returns {.doc-returns}

::: {.doc-definition-items}
<code> [DataFrame]{.doc-parameter-annotation}</code>

:   A one-row model-level summary.
:::

## Examples {.doc-examples}

Glance at a fitted Cox model for its overall fit statistics:

::: {#9d6ab448 .cell execution_count=1}
``` {.python .cell-code}
import greenwood as gw

# Load data, build a right-censored response, and fit a Cox model
lung = gw.load_dataset("lung", backend="polars")
y = gw.Surv.right(lung["time"], event=(lung["status"] == 2))
cox = gw.CoxPH().fit(y, covariates=lung[["age", "sex"]])

# Glance at overall model-fit statistics
gw.glance(cox, format="polars")
```

